{"body": "The bug appears when you have two keys, being one a subset of the other, like:\r\n\r\n```ruby\r\n{:phone => \"is not valid\", :phone_work => \"can't be blank\" }\r\n````\r\n\r\nSo the key length matter because if you don\u00b4t order by length the detect could give a false positive if the subset key is received first, without the ordering step, the result looks like this:\r\n\r\n```ruby\r\n{:phone => [\"is not valid\", \"work can't be blank\"]}\r\n```", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/4201144", "created_at": "2012-02-27T19:34:44Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/5169#issuecomment-4201144", "updated_at": "2012-02-27T19:34:44Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 5169, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/salrepe/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/salrepe/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/salrepe/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/salrepe", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/salrepe/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/salrepe", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/salrepe/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/84e56530282ccd0e9a23fd81ecdadd12?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F8aeb90a43d5237b8df2b3b2b308f7fa7.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/salrepe/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/salrepe/received_events", "gravatar_id": "84e56530282ccd0e9a23fd81ecdadd12", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/salrepe/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "salrepe", "type": "User", "id": 68961, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/salrepe/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "52381be1bd3543c15100e45d"}, "id": 4201144, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/5169"}
